Lehecka will need to use everything he has learned when he faces 2022 champion Alcaraz on Tuesday. Alcaraz leads Lehecka 2-1 in their Lexus ATP Head2Head series, but the 23-year-old Czech will take confidence from his victory against the Spaniard earlier this year in Doha. 

“Jiri is dangerous and these matches that of course he already played with Carlos can help him for the match,” said Navratil, who added that the more Lehecka competes against the best players, he is not as fearful when playing them. 

“This is also the most important thing, because when you have a big respect, then of course, it's hard to manage it. But if you understand these guys are playable and you can do it, then it's easier, because, [as] I've been trying to explain him, everybody's beatable.”



